 Port Elizabeth - The Family Violence Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit in Port Elizabeth are urgently trying to trace an 16 year old girl from Booysens Park in Bethelsdorp. Police spokesperson, Capt Sandra Janse Van Rensburg, said that Anita Karelse, was last seen on the 29 June 2019 and was only reported missing on Thursday. "According to her parents, this is not the first time that she went missing and they suspected that she may return home," she added. "During 2018, her parents reported her missing and after her friends informed her that the South African Police Service was looking for her she returned home. "It is suspected that that Karelse is in the Zwide vicinity." Capt Janse Van Rensburg said that she was wearing a black cap, White Uzzi top, maroon skirt and black pump tekkies. "Anyone who may have seen her or may know of her whereabouts is asked to contact D/Sgt Kelibone Mokhadla on 071 475 2327 or 041 401 3000 or Crime Stop 08600 10111 or their nearest police station." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 